        public void toMainScreen​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)

        This is the method for the cancel button. When the Cancel button is clicked, the Add Product form is closed and the user is returned to the Main Screen.

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - loads specified screen

      • saveNewProduct

        public void saveNewProduct​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        This is the method for the Save button. This method contains the functionality that checks to ensure the inventory, min , and max values all follow the rules. This method also populates a product instance in the Products table on the Main Screen with the values entered for the new product on the Add Product screen. An error message is thrown if the user enters input that does not match the variable type for that field.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - - the new product is added to the Product table on the Main Screen when Save is clicked. The user is returned to the Main Screen.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Input Invalid

      • addPartToNewProduct

        public void addPartToNewProduct​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This is the method for the Add button. This method grabs the data for the part highlighted in the Parts table on the Add Product screen and adds it to the Associated Parts table. This method associates a chosen part with a new product.If no part is selected before Add is clicked, and error message is thrown.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - - when the Add button is clicked, the Associated Parts table populates with the part chosen.

      • APFPartsSearchOnEnter

        public void APFPartsSearchOnEnter​(javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent keyEvent)
        This is the method to search the Parts table. This method grabs the input from the search field, trims it, and calls the method to find the search input from the Inventory class. If the search input is a number, the method for finding a part by ID number is called from the Inventory class. If the search field contains input that is not found in the part name or ID fields on the part table, an error message is thrown. If the search field is left empty when this method is called, it returns populates the table with all the current parts in the allParts list in Inventory. LOGICAL ERROR - A runtime error occurred when enter was pressed for the search field. Nothing was being returned. I had not tied the keyEvent to a specific key on the keyboard. Once I used the KeyCode method, the problem was resolved.
        Parameters:
        keyEvent - - this method is called when the user clicks the Search field and presses enter.

      • removeAssociatedPart

        public void removeAssociatedPart​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This method disassociates a part from a new part and removes the associates part from the Associated Parts table. When the user presses the Remove Associated Part button, the selected part is deleted from the Associated Parts table and not saved with the new part. A confirmation error is generated when an associated part is selected and the Remove Associated Part button is selected. An error message is thrown if no part is selected and button pressed.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - - this method is called when the Remove Associated Part button is selected by the user.

      • APFUpdatePartTable

        public void APFUpdatePartTable()
        This method sets the Part Table. This method populates the Part table on the Add Part screen with the same data that populates the Part table on the Main Screen.

      • APFUpdateAssociatedPartTable

        public void APFUpdateAssociatedPartTable()
        This method sets the Associated Parts Table. This method populates the Associated Parts Table with the data stored in the associatedParts list.

      • createNewId
